node.title: How a cocaine kingpin infiltrated the horseracing industry, and how it could happen again
node.description: An ABC investigation reveals how weak regulation allowed cocaine kingpin Damion Flower to help bankroll Australia's richest horse race, even though his horse business was running at a loss.

node.title: 'Staggering': UK braces for more COVID-19 cases as it hits new daily record
node.description: More than 78,000 new daily cases in the UK are recorded as the head of the UK Health Security Agency warns there could be a "staggering" amount of new COVID-19 cases in the country over the next few days

node.title: Lower KiwiSaver fees do not result in better performance - report
node.description: A new report looking into KiwiSaver's default fund changes has found lower fees do not help investors with better returns.
